N:harness
D:"Design a project-specific harness that defines agent roles, skill packages, orchestration topology, and validation workflow. Use when the user wants to build a harness for a project, design an agent team, scaffold domain skills, or translate a Claude-style team architecture to Codex, Gemini, OpenCode, Antigravity, Pi, or Claw-style runtimes."
G:harness|agent-team|skill-architect|orchestrator|multi-agent|topology|claude|codex|gemini|opencode|antigravity|pi|claw
U[5]:
  Build a neutral harness before writing one-off prompts
  Choose an architecture pattern that matches the work
  Translate Claude-native team concepts into adapter mode for other runtimes
  Scaffold a reusable .harness workspace with bundled script support
  Validate triggers and with-skill-vs-baseline outcomes
S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Frame,Extract domain outputs runtime and validation targets before naming agents
  2,Topology,Choose pipeline fan-out/fan-in producer-reviewer expert-pool supervisor or hybrid
  3,Mode,Use Claude native mode only when native team primitives exist; otherwise switch to adapter mode
  4,Scaffold,bash .agent-skills/harness/scripts/bootstrap-harness.sh --root . --platform codex --team-name review-team --mode hybrid
  5,Artifacts,Define agent roster skill map orchestrator contract and validation plan
  6,Validate,Use references/validation-playbook.md for trigger checks dry runs and baseline comparisons
R[4]:
  Keep neutral artifacts under .harness first, then map outward to platform-specific surfaces
  Do not claim TeamCreate or teammate messaging on platforms that do not expose them
  Use references for large pattern detail rather than bloating SKILL.md
  Validation is part of the harness, not a postscript
E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Claude harness","Build a harness for this project with analyst builder and QA teammates","Returns a Claude-native team plan plus reusable harness artifacts"
  "Codex adapter","Translate our Claude harness into a Codex-compatible workflow","Returns neutral artifacts and adapter mapping without fake native-team claims"
  "Domain skill factory","Design a harness for a legal review workflow","Returns topology skill boundaries validation steps and scaffolded directories"
